race.comment: TIVACI CODE (8) improved as expected at his second start, placing second behind a dominant winner at Ballarat over 1500m. Draws an inside gate, and John Allen sticking aboard is a positive. He's ready to win. KRISTY SABEEL (5) resumed with a placing at Hamilton over 1400m and there was merit in that given he's been off the scene for 651 days. Should enjoy a soft run and the step up in trip will suit. Ditto with LIMOSA (6), who settled back off a wide gate in the same contest, but was working into it late. Third up and will keep improving. No surprise to see more from BOSS BOY (2) up from a mile. Peaks and the blinkers go on for the first time. VALIANT SUN (9) had no in the same contest on debut. Maps well today and shapes as a quick improver.
